cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the performance of dynamic TDD in small cell networks from a media access control (MAC) layer viewpoint, which is closely related to network protocols and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper also involves information theory (cs.IT), multimedia (cs.MM), system and control (cs.SY), and cryptography and security (cs.CR) aspects, which are relevant to the study of dynamic TDD.
